<text>When my family and I leave for vacations (averaging 4 days or so), we have my dog board here.

Upon seeing the place in which my dog would stay, I was so sad to see that the conditions were/are very poor. The hospital's website states: "On occasion when we go out of town we need a place for our furry family member to stay while we are gone. Your pet can stay in a temperature controlled environment where he/she will be loved and cared for by our staff. He/she will stay in a spacious dog run with views of his/her neighbors and talk to the others about their great family and how much they are loved."

This is all complete bullshit. They sleep in caged, wired boxes(essentially) on a cold, hard cement floor. I hope that they at least provide them with a blanket considering they are sleeping on bare cement and during the winter time. The dogs in there are miserable; though it is true the dogs will view their "neighbors", it is because they have so little space. I do not buy any of their tempered, cutesy rhetoric. The staff are both nice and lifeless, basically.

I cannot speak for their medical services because my pet has only received shots from this place, no surgery or urgent medical treatment.

Tl;dr - if you love your pet, please do not board them here. You get what you pay for<//text>< pics>

< Review>
DISHONEST:  They are dishonest about the actual total cost of services until AFTER they have given the services and you are forced to pay for it.  They were not upfront about the actual cost of services!  After my cat was seen by the doctor, another man named Omar, a nurse I think, came in and quoted me a price for the services that the doctor recommended.  I specifically asked him "what is the total out the door price that I am looking at for this list of services", and he said "$220 for the whole thing."  Based on this total price he told me, I said okay go ahead.  When I went outside to pay a deposit, the receptionist told me the total charges were $306 for the exact same list of services.  After a few moments of disagreement on the price, I reluctantly agreed to $306 since my cat was in pain and needed to be cared for.
The next day, a man who sounded like Omar, called me and told me that my pet needed additional services.  Again I asked him twice "what will be the TOTAL additional charges for all these additional services," and he said "a total of $70 more."  I said "okay, go ahead, but not for more than $70."  When I went to pick up my cat later that day, the front receptionist actually charged me $158 in additional fees.  The total cost that was quoted to me for these services for the two days was $290, but they actually charged me $464 for the exact same list of services.  Nothing additional was done to even begin to justify the higher fee.
This technique that they used of quoting me a lower price before the services were rendered, and the inflated price they actually charged for the same exact list of services when I went to pay is very deceptive and dishonest!  They were not honest about their pricing upfront even when I specifically ask them what the total cost is or will be.< /Review>

< Review>
I went in thinking it was just an ordinary teriyaki place, and came out convinced that there is no comparison to others ok have visited.
By far this takes the lead on taste and freshness of ingredients, the side vegetable salad they served was way too little but it was very good.
If you have liked Panda Express taste, get ready for a little better than that way this particular place, I wouldn't be surprised to see them expanding very soon, they really are good and the place looks very clean.
Good experience over all.
The only thing I would improve would be the menu presentation, I would pay attention into making it a little more visually appealing, the food is very good though.< /Review>

<Text>I have been going to Teriyaki Time for over a year now and their food and service has been consistently amazing. My wife and I enjoy their Thai Chicken, Teriyaki Chicken, and also their Sweet Spicy Chicken. These items are all grilled. We also order the Miso soup as well. The food service size is big. You could share a meal or save for second meal.

We were there one day and our order was a little late to serve. The manager gave us complimentary potstickers while we waited. My wife and I were so impressed by their service. I showed my brother this place and his is also so addicted to it.

I would go here because they are a small restaurant and keeping restaurants like this in business is very important. They are a gem.< /Text><Time>1483808411100<//Time><user>112386787709261977828< /user>< Rating>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
Halmar is a great find because they sell quality work clothes at several price points and they tell you like it is.  They have lots of bandanas, priced reasonably, as well as rugged clothing, including offerings by Ben Davis, Carhartt, and some European brands not found elsewhere. I usually stock up here seasonally, whether gearing up for crisp autumn weather or warm summer projects. Very popular gear with my teenage daughter and twenty one year old son. This is an independent store and the owner is a good guy. I trust him.< /text>

< Review>
This place has lots of great work clothes, but the person running the counter (owner?) and his attitude caused me to leave with out buying what I needed. I was permitted into the gated front door and asked to leave my bag at the counter. I browsed while he helped two other people at the counter. No major objection there, but when another person came to the gate, he told them he was closed and not open for another hour or so. I overheard him disparage that person to the other customers because he appeared homeless and was carrying a lot of bags. For the remainder of my short visit, and in loud conversation with the other customers he also praised the Trump wall and suggested that a customer that called asking for medical scrubs was not involved with work for real men. All with a polite and friendly demeanor. True, I don't agree with his politics, but I also don't want to do business with some one who acts one way towards people and then speaks disparagingly of them openly to other customers. Bad form for a salesperson and a business owner.< /Review>

<text>Largest 99 Cents Only store I have ever shopped at. So much stuff in a 99 store!

Was in the area and decided to stop by for a few things. To my great frustration the most important item that I wanted was out of stock and they didn't know when more would be available.

As already stated this place is big and, somewhat, opposing. Rather a chilly, cold atmosphere.

Many, many employees all over the place stocking and replenishing shelves and displays. Floors with a glossy appearance.

At the check out counter as the cashier tallied my purchases, she, seemingly, reluctantly asked if I had found everything okay. "Yes, except for one item", I said.

104151835960642222580< /user>
< username>
Jose A. Camacho T.< /username>
<time>1552464356968</time><rate>5</rate>< Text>
Since Google will only allow one review per location. I will be doing an extensive review. I've mostly been here for piercings.

I had a tattoo touched up by Aya, she did a good job and I didn't have any issues with scarring, fading, or healing.

Now for the bulk of my review: Piercings. I came here for the first time on April 20, 2018 to get two bottom lip piercings, snake bites. That first experience was very pleasant. Their piercer, Kim, did a great job about explaining the process, and the aftercare of the piercings. I fell in love with my piercings and decided to go back about a month later to get two more lip piercings done. Again, Kim was thorough about the process and aftercare. A few months later I returned and had her pierce my septum. Just a few months ago I went back and had her do my nostrils, bridge, and a dermal in between my brows. Each time she has been consistently thorough about explaining the process, and being professional through the entire process. She is very accessible to helping with issues that may arise. For example: On my first pair of lip piercings the jewelry was too small and we came to a solution.

I want to add this specific paragraph to address some comments I saw in other reviews, specifically about the bridge piercing since I have one myself. People have to understand that a bridge piercing has a higher risk of migrating or rejecting, actually Kim explains things like that before she does the piercings. Another thing, is you have to be patient and really be satisfied with the placement she marks before actually piercing you. When I did my bridge with her, I had to have her mark the placement like 3 times before I was certain that it was where I wanted it, and where it would look good with how I would be wearing it long term.

Overall, the staff here is professional and the shop gives you a cozy, at-home feeling. My experiences here over the last year have been only positive. Actually might go get my tongue and nipples pierced soon.</Text>

< Text>
First time there so take these observations with a grain of salt. At 2 pm the place wasn't busy.  I had the hot pastrami sandwich. While some of the pastrami slices were a bit too fatty for my taste, the taste was a ten. Very complimentary interaction with the secondary ingredients. The bread was soft, warm and salty tasty. Surprisingly pleasant interaction of the component flavors given their simplicity. My wife tried the the french dip sandwich. A favorite of hers,  she uses this dish as a yardstick against which she compares other restaurants' versions.  As they used to say in days of yore, she was "smackin' her lips". Give it a visit if either of those 2 dishes sound good to you. We plan to go back to try some of the other offerings.< /Text>

<Pics>None< /Pics>< resp>

< gmapID>
0x80d9450f6a9e8745:0xc9842bf1044682bb< /gmapID>
< text>
Really like this place for a quick bite when I'm in the mood for a sandwich. Of course, the Turkado is my choice. Try it toasted and melted... it's a whole new side of everyone's favorite. It's the only way I'll get it now.

The vibe of the place is a cool PB 90's beach theme which definitely is fitting for the fare of food. The beer selection is sort of limited, and since they only serve beer, sometimes it can be a struggle to find something for those of us who can't do the IPAs. My personal choice is the Cali Creamin' beer from Mother Earth. It's a light beer with a creamy and slight vanilla taste. Ask for a sample of it, or anything! All beers on tap are conveniently listed on their digital tap screen.

In a perfect world, Board & Brew would have a full bar. I've asked them if there's any chance, and the answer was no... but please, management, if you're reading this, PLEASE strongly consider a full bar. I'm not a big beer drinker, and this would totally be the icing on the cake for a great happy hour spot.</text>

But then, their service department looked busy AF, like they never expected to have so many cars in a day to be serviced. Would I go back? ehhhh... I dislike that you cant make an appointment for an oil change, but I don't think that would change anything. The staff was nice, I can't lie about that. I'll give them another shot and my rating may change.<//Review>

Dishonest sales person and unreasonable pricing. I really wanted the color they had so I drove almost 200 miles, one way, to get it but it didn't have all the features that the same car, different color, had at Hoblit. Lampe advertised theirs for $42+K while Hoblit had it for $41K. That is ~$3K of differences. I tried to negotiate and the sales person said what they have more than others is a Life Time Warranty. I could not believe that this even exist so I asked for a document to prove it. They first gave me a print out of the regular limited warranty and when I told them its limited in time they went back and force and started to come with various excuses of why they don't have a document. One of the ridicules excuses was that the contract with Finance will have a box to check and that would give me the Life Time Warranty.  When Chris couldn't prove it he said "Trust Me." What a joke.  I had to leave the first day and drove  back the next day because I really wanted that color and thought I could maybe negotiate adding an $800 hitch installed for free to offset some of the missing features. I was willing to pay a bit more just to get this color. He said he'll double check then he called back and finally admitted that they don't have it. Big trap and I'm sure many people may have fallen for it.
